-- Typo-binder hint: `gren` in the LAST arm is a fresh binder (the resolver
-- silently falls back when a pattern name is no known constructor), so the
-- match is exhaustive and nothing follows it — invisible to both the
-- missing and redundancy warnings, yet `f green` now returns 2 by
-- accident of arm order rather than by matching a constructor. The
-- SInfo-severity hint (captured in this fixture's golden) points at the
-- resemblance to the uncovered constructor `green`. Never blocking.
DECLARE Color IS ONE OF red, green, blue

GIVEN c IS A Color
GIVETH A NUMBER
f c MEANS
  CONSIDER c
  WHEN red THEN 1
  WHEN blue THEN 3
  WHEN gren THEN 2

#EVAL f green
